The paper deals with geometric spanners, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of robustness is related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS), and the paper presents a new construction algorithm for spanners, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of $\mathcal{O}$-notation suggests that the paper involves some analysis of the running time or complexity of the algorithm, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper presents a practical application of spanners in network design, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
